The paper deals with the implementation of millimeter wave (mmWave) multiuser multiple-input multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also considers the practical hardware impairments, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of hybrid digital analog (HDA) beamforming is a technique used in mmWave communication systems, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.AR).
